Random Forest Analysis Exploration for DMX Linkages

Rachael Blake

January 27, 2016

###
# Pink Salmon
CPD_Pink <- CPD %>% 
            select(PDO_anul_mn,NPGO_anul_mn,#WndSp_m_s_AnnMn,WndDir_degT_AnnMn,
                   log_WTemp_C_AnnMn,AnnChl,log_SwdLineMayEuphausiids,
                   log_SwdLineMayCopepods,goaPinkCatchNum,
                   PWS_WildPinkSalmon_SSB_ModelOutput,ArrAdult,
                   Poll_Yr3plus_TtlBmss_1000Tons) %>%
            filter(complete.cases(.))
goaPink <- randomForest(PWS_WildPinkSalmon_SSB_ModelOutput ~., data=CPD_Pink, importance=T, do.trace=1000, ntree=5000)
##      |      Out-of-bag   |
## Tree |      MSE  %Var(y) |
## 1000 | 2.842e+13    86.03 |
## 2000 | 2.859e+13    86.55 |
## 3000 | 2.902e+13    87.84 |
## 4000 | 2.911e+13    88.11 |
## 5000 | 2.895e+13    87.62 |
print(goaPink)
## 
## Call:
##  randomForest(formula = PWS_WildPinkSalmon_SSB_ModelOutput ~ .,      data = CPD_Pink, importance = T, do.trace = 1000, ntree = 5000) 
##                Type of random forest: regression
##                      Number of trees: 5000
## No. of variables tried at each split: 3
## 
##           Mean of squared residuals: 2.894613e+13
##                     % Var explained: 12.38
plot(goaPink)

varImpPlot(goaPink)

goaPink$importance
##                                     %IncMSE IncNodePurity
## PDO_anul_mn                    6.206695e+11  3.233750e+13
## NPGO_anul_mn                  -9.447830e+11  5.965804e+13
## log_WTemp_C_AnnMn             -5.406191e+11  5.631600e+13
## AnnChl                        -1.605990e+11  5.525106e+13
## log_SwdLineMayEuphausiids     -9.410104e+11  1.909607e+13
## log_SwdLineMayCopepods        -3.163728e+09  1.109002e+13
## goaPinkCatchNum                1.049842e+13  1.002252e+14
## ArrAdult                      -1.177470e+11  1.073143e+13
## Poll_Yr3plus_TtlBmss_1000Tons  4.002160e+11  1.992788e+13
Imp_Var(goaPink) # get important variables
## [1] 1.049842e+13
#  important variables below
partialPlot(goaPink,CPD_Pink,goaPinkCatchNum)

# Arrowtooth
CPD_Arrow <- CPD %>% 
             select(PDO_anul_mn,NPGO_anul_mn,#WndSp_m_s_AnnMn,WndDir_degT_AnnMn,
                    log_WTemp_C_AnnMn,AnnChl,log_SwdLineMayEuphausiids,
                    log_Poll_Age1_recruits_millions, ArrAdult,arth_tons,
                    arth_real_rev,arth_vessels,arth_processors,arth_real_price) %>%
             filter(complete.cases(.))
arrow <- randomForest(ArrAdult ~., data=CPD_Arrow, importance=T, do.trace=1000, ntree=5000)
##      |      Out-of-bag   |
## Tree |      MSE  %Var(y) |
## 1000 | 1.265e+10    30.78 |
## 2000 | 1.274e+10    31.02 |
## 3000 | 1.284e+10    31.25 |
## 4000 | 1.307e+10    31.81 |
## 5000 | 1.325e+10    32.24 |
print(arrow)
## 
## Call:

##                Type of random forest: regression
##                      Number of trees: 5000
## No. of variables tried at each split: 3
## 
##           Mean of squared residuals: 13248307914

# Pollock Adults

                   ArrAdult, PCod_female_Bmss_t,hlbt_pounds,

# Halibut

           select(PDO_anul_mn,NPGO_anul_mn,#WndSp_m_s_AnnMn,WndDir_degT_AnnMn,

                  log_Poll_Age1_recruits_millions, TotTCrab,log_Pink_Shrimp,
